abstract: Results of a new poll of potential Democratic presidential contenders reflect the party’s debate over whether to opt for an experienced hand or a fresh face.
snippet: Results of a new poll of potential Democratic presidential contenders reflect the party’s debate over whether to opt for an experienced hand or a fresh face.
lead_paragraph: An early poll of Iowa Democratic voters looking for a challenger to unseat President Trump shows them torn between familiar candidates in their 70s and one lightly experienced newcomer who is 46.
